name: UnmodifiableSetView
comment:
An unmodifiable set.

An UnmodifiableSetView contains a unmodifiable_collection/dart-core.Set object and ensures that it does not change. Methods that would change the set, such as unmodifiable_collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableSetMixin.add and unmodifiable_collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableSetMixin.remove, throw an unmodifiable_collection/dart-core.UnsupportedError. Permitted operations defer to the wrapped set.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment:
Provides an iterator that iterates over the elements of this set.

The order of iteration is defined by the individual Set implementation, but must be consistent between changes to the set.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in the iterable.

This is an efficient operation that doesn't require iterating through the elements.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.map.f multiple times on the same element.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function test multiple times on the same element.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.contains.value is in the set.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate test. Returns false otherwise.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.join.separator string.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate test. Returns false otherwise.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.take.n elements.

It is an error if unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.skipWhile.test.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.elementAt.indexth element.

The unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than unmodifiable_collection/dart-core.IterableBase.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.elementAt.index elements in this.

add.name: add
add.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

lookup.name: lookup
lookup.comment:
If an object equal to unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.lookup.object is in the set, return it.

Checks if there is an object in the set that is equal to unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.lookup.object. If so, that object is returned, otherwise returns null.

removeAll.name: removeAll
removeAll.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

retainAll.name: retainAll
retainAll.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.

containsAll.name: containsAll
containsAll.comment: Returns whether this Set contains all the elements of unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.containsAll.other.

intersection.name: intersection
intersection.comment:
Returns a new set which is the intersection between this set and unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.intersection.other.

That is, the returned set contains all the elements of this dart-core.Set that are also elements of unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.intersection.other according to other.contains.

union.name: union
union.comment:
Returns a new set which contains all the elements of this set and unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.union.other.

That is, the returned set contains all the elements of this dart-core.Set and all the elements of unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.union.other.

difference.name: difference
difference.comment:
Returns a new set with the the elements of this that are not in unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.difference.other.

That is, the returned set contains all the elements of this dart-core.Set that are not elements of unmodifiable_collection/unmodifiable_collection.UnmodifiableSetView.difference.other according to other.contains.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError; operations that change the set are disallowed.
